HEADWORD: Goniatite
<hw>Go"ni*a*tite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
angle.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>One of an extinct genus of
fossil cephalopods, allied to the Ammonites. The earliest forms are
found in the Devonian formation, the latest, in the Triassic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

